The bug has been successfully fixed! Here's a summary of what was done:

## Problem Analysis
The issue was in the `deserializeUsingPropertyBasedWithUnwrapped` method in `BeanDeserializer.java`. When deserializing beans with both creator properties and unwrapped properties, there was a bug in how properties appearing after the last creator property were handled.

Specifically, in the while loop that copies remaining tokens to the buffer after all creator properties are processed, the code was calling `p.nextToken()` before `tokens.copyCurrentStructure(p)`. This caused the parser to advance past the field name before copying, meaning only the values (not the field names) were being copied to the token buffer.

## The Bug
```java
// BUGGY CODE:
while (t == JsonToken.FIELD_NAME) {
    // NOTE: do NOT skip name as it needs to be copied; `copyCurrentStructure` does that
    p.nextToken();                 // Parser moved to VALUE, skipping FIELD_NAME!
    tokens.copyCurrentStructure(p); // Only copies the value, not field name + value
    t = p.nextToken();
}
```

## The Fix
```java
// FIXED CODE:
while (t == JsonToken.FIELD_NAME) {
    // NOTE: do NOT skip name as it needs to be copied; `copyCurrentStructure` does that
    tokens.copyCurrentStructure(p); // Parser at FIELD_NAME, copies name and value
    t = p.nextToken();
}
```

## Verification
- The triggering test `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.struct.TestUnwrapped::testIssue2088UnwrappedFieldsAfterLastCreatorProp` now passes
- The fix ensures that properties appearing after the last creator property in JSON are properly copied with both field names and values to the token buffer for unwrapped property handling

The patch has been saved to `blind_fix.patch` and contains the minimal, targeted fix for this specific issue.

